00:15:04,369 --> 00:15:05,936
- [laughs]

252
00:15:05,937 --> 00:15:08,305
OH, THAT'S THE ONE THING:

253
00:15:08,306 --> 00:15:10,407
SHITTY CELL SERVICE.

254
00:15:10,408 --> 00:15:12,776
- YEAH, SEE, I KNEW IT WAS
TOO GOOD TO BE TRUE.

255
00:15:12,777 --> 00:15:14,311
- HEY, STOP IT!
- I'M OUT!

256
00:15:14,312 --> 00:15:17,881
[laughing]

257
00:15:19,116 --> 00:15:21,318
- WHAT DID YOU PAY
FOR THIS PLACE?

258
00:15:21,319 --> 00:15:24,421
- 10 GRAND.
- 10 GRAND.

259
00:15:24,422 --> 00:15:25,989
- EVERYTHING IN MY SAVINGS.

260
00:15:25,990 --> 00:15:27,791
- THAT'S, LIKE, FREE.

261
00:15:27,792 --> 00:15:29,059
WHY?

262
00:15:29,060 --> 00:15:31,127
- BECAUSE THIS IS
THE MIDDLE OF NOWHERE,

263
00:15:31,128 --> 00:15:32,929
AND NO ONE ELSE WANTS TO BE
OUT HERE.

264
00:15:32,930 --> 00:15:34,531
- [laughing]

265
00:15:34,532 --> 00:15:37,968
I'M SORRY I WAS SUCH A BITCH.
I'M SORRY.

266
00:15:37,969 --> 00:15:40,504
I'VE JUST BEEN STRESSED OUT
AND...

267
00:15:40,505 --> 00:15:43,006
- HEY, IT'S OKAY.
AT LEAST WE HAVE EACH OTHER.

268
00:15:43,007 --> 00:15:44,708
- THAT BETTER BE ENOUGH,

269
00:15:44,709 --> 00:15:46,577
BECAUSE WITH A HOUSE
IN BUMFUCK, EGYPT,

270
00:15:46,578 --> 00:15:48,545
WE REALLY DON'T HAVE
MUCH CHOICE.

271
00:15:48,546 --> 00:15:50,614
- JUST WAIT UNTIL YOU SEE
THE REST OF IT.

272
00:15:50,615 --> 00:15:52,983
DON'T MESS WITH A GUY
THAT'S IN LOVE, ALL RIGHT?

273
00:15:52,984 --> 00:15:55,051
- [laughs]

274
00:15:55,052 --> 00:15:58,054
[ominous music]

275
00:15:58,055 --> 00:16:00,891
 

276
00:16:00,892 --> 00:16:03,293
[clamoring]
GOT IT?

277
00:16:03,294 --> 00:16:06,430
WOW.
LOOK AT THIS PLACE.

278
00:16:06,431 --> 00:16:08,265
THIS IS EXCITING, BABE.

279
00:16:08,266 --> 00:16:09,833
- YEAH.

280
00:16:12,904 --> 00:16:13,970
YEAH.

281
00:16:13,971 --> 00:16:15,138
- I'M READY.

282
00:16:15,139 --> 00:16:17,207
- HOPEFULLY OUR KEY'S
GOING TO WORK.

283
00:16:21,846 --> 00:16:23,814
- OOH.

284
00:16:23,815 --> 00:16:26,182
THAT'S AN INTERESTING SMELL.

285
00:16:26,183 --> 00:16:27,818
- SMELLS LIKE
YOUR BELLY BUTTON.

286
00:16:27,819 --> 00:16:31,988
- [laughing]

287
00:16:31,989 --> 00:16:34,157
THAT IS JUST SEXY.

288
00:16:34,158 --> 00:16:37,528
- LET'S GET SOME LIGHTS.

289
00:16:37,529 --> 00:16:39,062
DAMN.

290
00:16:39,063 --> 00:16:40,464
I CALLED TO GET
THE POWER TURNED ON,

291
00:16:40,465 --> 00:16:42,198
BUT I GUESS
THEY NEVER MADE IT.

292
00:16:42,199 --> 00:16:44,568
- WHAT?
NO SOLAR PANELS?

293
00:16:44,569 --> 00:16:46,837
NOT VERY GREEN OF YOU.

294
00:16:46,838 --> 00:16:49,139
[flicking light switch]

295
00:16:49,140 --> 00:16:53,076
- DAMN.

296
00:16:53,077 --> 00:16:55,278
[flicking light switch]

297
00:16:55,279 --> 00:16:57,414
WE GOT PLATES.

298
00:16:57,415 --> 00:17:01,452
- NO, EVAN.
THIS IS ANTIQUE CHINA.

299
00:17:01,453 --> 00:17:04,354
THIS IS REAL SILVER.

300
00:17:04,355 --> 00:17:06,690
LIKE, WHY WOULD THEY LEAVE
THIS STUFF BEHIND?

301
00:17:06,691 --> 00:17:10,327
IT'S, LIKE, GOT TO BE
FAMILY HEIRLOOMS OR SOMETHING.

302
00:17:10,328 --> 00:17:12,496
- THE CONTRACT SAID WE GET
ALL THE FURNISHINGS.

303
00:17:12,497 --> 00:17:15,332
- REALLY?

304
00:17:15,333 --> 00:17:17,734
[laughing]

305
00:17:18,803 --> 00:17:21,304
THIS PLACE IS INCREDIBLE.

306
00:17:21,305 --> 00:17:22,573
- RIGHT?

307
00:17:22,574 --> 00:17:25,108
- THE DOWNSTAIRS IS BIGGER
THAN OUR APARTMENT.

308
00:17:25,109 --> 00:17:28,044
- WAIT FOR IT.
WAIT FOR IT.

309
00:17:28,045 --> 00:17:30,313
- OH.

310
00:17:30,314 --> 00:17:33,717
THIS STOVE IS AMAZING.

311
00:17:33,718 --> 00:17:35,185
- I KNEW YOU'D LOVE THAT THING.

312
00:17:35,186 --> 00:17:38,989
- OH, I THINK I ACTUALLY SAW
SOME POTS AND PANS.

313
00:17:38,990 --> 00:17:41,024
- YEAH, THERE SHOULD BE
EVERYTHING THAT WE NEED HERE,

314
00:17:41,025 --> 00:17:42,025
PRETTY MUCH.

315
00:17:42,026 --> 00:17:43,026
IT CAME PRETTY LOADED.

316
00:17:43,027 --> 00:17:44,294
- THERE THEY ARE.

317
00:17:44,295 --> 00:17:49,099
- ALL RIGHT, GIRL.
I KNEW YOU'D FIND THEM.

318
00:17:49,100 --> 00:17:51,067
HEY, REMEMBER,
IF YOU FIND AN OLD TWINKIE,

319
00:17:51,068 --> 00:17:52,603
IT'S STILL GOOD.

320
00:17:52,604 --> 00:17:55,071
- [laughing]
THAT'S REALLY GROSS.

321
00:17:58,610 --> 00:18:00,611
LOOK, BABE.

322
00:18:00,612 --> 00:18:02,045
WE GOT RUNNING WATER.

323
00:18:02,046 --> 00:18:03,547
WATER COMPANY MUST HAVE COME.

324
00:18:03,548 --> 00:18:04,648
- HMM.

325
00:18:04,649 --> 00:18:06,282
BUT IT'S RUN
ON AN ELECTRIC WELL.

326
00:18:06,283 --> 00:18:07,751
OH, YOU KNOW WHAT?

327
00:18:07,752 --> 00:18:11,321
HEY, HOLD ON A SECOND.
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

328
00:18:20,398 --> 00:18:23,666
HMM.

329
00:18:27,738 --> 00:18:30,740
[tense music]

330
00:18:30,741 --> 00:18:37,047
 

331
00:18:37,048 --> 00:18:38,648
WHAT THE HELL?

332
00:18:46,324 --> 00:18:48,158
WHAT THE HECK IS THIS?

333
00:18:48,159 --> 00:18:56,099
 

334
00:19:07,312 --> 00:19:09,146
HUH.

335
00:19:12,216 --> 00:19:13,216
- EASY, KID.

336
00:19:13,217 --> 00:19:14,217
rip!

337
00:19:14,218 --> 00:19:15,218
- FUCK!

338
00:19:15,219 --> 00:19:16,619
- DAMN!

339
00:19:16,620 --> 00:19:18,455
SCRAPPY LITTLE
SON OF A BITCH.

340
00:19:18,456 --> 00:19:21,992
- [breathing heavily]

341
00:19:24,062 --> 00:19:25,562
WHAT THE FUCK'S
YOUR PROBLEM, MAN?

342
00:19:25,563 --> 00:19:27,497
- HEY.

343
00:19:34,205 --> 00:19:38,108
YOU'RE ONE OF THEM
SENSITIVE BOYS, AIN'T YA?

344
00:19:38,109 --> 00:19:40,543
AIN'T A THING
TO BE ASHAMED OF.

345
00:19:40,544 --> 00:19:44,948
A LOT OF PEOPLE LIKE THAT.

346
00:19:44,949 --> 00:19:46,583
YOU KNOW I'M HERE
TO TURN YOU ON, RIGHT?

347
00:19:46,584 --> 00:19:47,584
- WHAT?

348
00:19:47,585 --> 00:19:49,719
- YOUR POWER.

349
00:19:49,720 --> 00:19:53,390
WANT YOUR HOUSE TO BURN DOWN?

350
00:19:54,758 --> 00:19:56,493
- THE BREAKER BOX IS OVER THERE.

351
00:19:56,494 --> 00:19:58,362
- I'LL TAKE CARE OF YA.

352
00:19:58,363 --> 00:20:00,864
I'LL TAKE CARE OF YA GOOD.

353
00:20:04,268 --> 00:20:08,171
- AH.

354
00:20:08,172 --> 00:20:10,407
OW.

355
00:20:14,945 --> 00:20:17,014
WHAT THE HELL?

356
00:20:23,354 --> 00:20:25,555
IS THIS NATIVE AMERICAN?

357
00:20:29,093 --> 00:20:30,060
[grunts]

358
00:20:35,766 --> 00:20:37,501
OH, SHIT!

359
00:20:37,502 --> 00:20:38,768
UGH!

360
00:20:43,007 --> 00:20:44,007
[sniffing]

361
00:20:44,008 --> 00:20:47,377
[groans]

362
00:20:47,378 --> 00:20:50,380
[eerie music]

363
00:20:50,381 --> 00:20:52,615
 

364
00:20:52,616 --> 00:20:54,351
COOL.

365
00:20:54,352 --> 00:21:02,292
 

366
00:21:27,385 --> 00:21:28,785
- OH, YEAH.

367
00:21:35,526 --> 00:21:37,827
THAT'S MY GIRL.

368
00:21:41,899 --> 00:21:43,166
THERE WE GO.

369
00:21:47,438 --> 00:21:50,440
[anxious music]

370
00:21:50,441 --> 00:21:57,914
 

371
00:21:57,915 --> 00:21:59,382
[buzzing]

372
00:22:09,494 --> 00:22:10,594
- OH!

373
00:22:10,595 --> 00:22:12,061
- WHOA!

374
00:22:12,062 --> 00:22:13,696
- OH, GOD!

375
00:22:13,697 --> 00:22:17,200
DON'T SNEAK UP ON ME
LIKE THAT.

376
00:22:17,201 --> 00:22:19,702
- OH, SHIT!

377
00:22:19,703 --> 00:22:21,438
THAT IS SO DISGUSTING.

378
00:22:21,439 --> 00:22:23,473
OH, IS THAT PINEAPPLE?

379
00:22:23,474 --> 00:22:24,508
I FUCKING HATE PINEAPPLE.

380
00:22:24,509 --> 00:22:25,808
- GET IT OUT OF HERE.

381
00:22:25,809 --> 00:22:27,377
- I THOUGHT THE KITCHEN
WAS YOUR DOMAIN.

382
00:22:27,378 --> 00:22:28,478
- EVAN REYNOLDS,

383
00:22:28,479 --> 00:22:29,912
IF YOU EVER WANT
TO SPEAK TO ME AGAIN,

384
00:22:29,913 --> 00:22:32,815
YOU WILL GET THAT THING
OUT OF HERE.

385
00:22:32,816 --> 00:22:34,851
- OKAY.

386
00:22:37,921 --> 00:22:39,523
[groaning]

387
00:22:39,524 --> 00:22:42,091
OKAY.
ALL RIGHT.

388
00:22:42,092 --> 00:22:43,460
COME ON, PORKY.

389
00:22:43,461 --> 00:22:45,928
LET'S GET YOU LORD OF THE FLIES
TO TAKE THE REST ON.

390
00:22:45,929 --> 00:22:47,964
[exhales deeply]

391
00:22:47,965 --> 00:22:49,266
- GO!
- I'M GOING.

392
00:22:49,267 --> 00:22:51,334
- UGH.

393
00:23:05,049 --> 00:23:06,883
[laughter]

394
00:23:06,884 --> 00:23:09,118
- UNLESS I'M MISTAKEN,

395
00:23:09,119 --> 00:23:10,420
I THINK IT'S BEER 30.

396
00:23:10,421 --> 00:23:14,724
- THAT SOUNDS GOOD.

397
00:23:14,725 --> 00:23:16,926
WHERE ARE WE STAYING
TONIGHT?

398
00:23:16,927 --> 00:23:18,127
- I BROUGHT THE CAMPING GEAR.

399
00:23:18,128 --> 00:23:21,731
- SEE, I WAS KIND OF THINKING
ABOUT THAT HOTEL

400
00:23:21,732 --> 00:23:22,932
OFF THE INTERSTATE...

401
00:23:22,933 --> 00:23:24,467
- THE ONE THAT'S, LIKE,
AN HOUR AWAY?

402
00:23:24,468 --> 00:23:26,936
- YEAH.
- COME ON.

403
00:23:26,937 --> 00:23:28,505
WE GOT TO STAY HERE
SOONER OR LATER.

404
00:23:28,506 --> 00:23:29,506
IT'LL BE FUN.

405
00:23:29,507 --> 00:23:32,008
- FUN?
- YES, FUN.

406
00:23:32,009 --> 00:23:34,244
YOU REMEMBER
WHAT FUN IS, RIGHT?

407
00:23:34,245 --> 00:23:36,979
- YEAH, I REMEMBER
WHAT FUN IS.

408
00:23:36,980 --> 00:23:38,215
YES.

409
00:23:38,216 --> 00:23:39,916
I LIKE FUN.
- YEAH?

410
00:23:39,917 --> 00:23:43,520
- YES, I LIKE FUN.

411
00:23:43,521 --> 00:23:45,822
- I KNEW YOU DID.

412
00:23:47,225 --> 00:23:50,227
[eerie orchestral music]

413
00:23:50,228 --> 00:23:56,233
 

414
00:23:56,234 --> 00:23:59,502
[crickets chirping]

415
00:24:03,574 --> 00:24:06,509
[creaking]

416
00:24:22,360 --> 00:24:23,926
bang!

417
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:32,001
- HEY.

418
00:24:32,002 --> 00:24:33,570
DID YOU HEAR THAT?

419
00:24:33,571 --> 00:24:38,241
- [mumbling] I DON'T KNOW.
NO.

420
00:24:38,242 --> 00:24:41,244
[ominous music]

421
00:24:41,245 --> 00:24:49,185
 

422
00:25:09,740 --> 00:25:15,345
- [heavy breathing]

423
00:25:15,346 --> 00:25:23,286
 

424
00:25:24,655 --> 00:25:27,457
- [giggling]

425
00:25:31,529 --> 00:25:32,895
- MARY, WHAT DID I TELL YOU

426
00:25:32,896 --> 00:25:35,064
ABOUT STAYING AWAY
FROM THAT BOY?

427
00:25:35,065 --> 00:25:37,133
- I WAS JUST--
- YOU WERE NOTHING.

428
00:25:37,134 --> 00:25:42,639
NOW GET OUT OF HERE
BEFORE I TELL YOUR MAMA.

429
00:25:42,640 --> 00:25:44,774
I'M GONNA COUNT TO THREE,

430
00:25:44,775 --> 00:25:49,912
AND THEN I'M GONNA MAKE YOU WISH
YOU WERE NEVER BORN.

431
00:25:49,913 --> 00:25:51,648
ONE...

432
00:25:51,649 --> 00:25:52,849
TWO...

433
00:25:59,089 --> 00:26:07,029
 

434
00:26:22,513 --> 00:26:23,847
- WHERE DID YOU GO?

435
00:26:23,848 --> 00:26:26,383
- I HAD TO TAKE CARE
OF SOME BURGLARS.

436
00:26:26,384 --> 00:26:28,852
- HMM.
THANKS, HONEY.

437
00:26:28,853 --> 00:26:30,754
- YOU'RE WELCOME.

438
00:26:36,827 --> 00:26:39,829
[jovial banjo music]

439
00:26:39,830 --> 00:26:46,035
 

440
00:26:46,036 --> 00:26:47,370
- OOH.

441
00:26:47,371 --> 00:26:49,406
- [laughing]

442
00:26:49,407 --> 00:26:51,875
OOH!

443
00:26:51,876 --> 00:26:53,576
- WHAT THE HELL IS THIS?

444
00:26:53,577 --> 00:26:57,881
- IT'S AN OLD-FASHIONED
IDIOT DETECTOR.

445
00:26:57,882 --> 00:27:01,451
AND LOOK--
IT'S WORKING.

446
00:27:01,452 --> 00:27:02,985
- I DON'T GET IT.

447
00:27:02,986 --> 00:27:04,754
- THAT'S 'CAUSE
YOU'RE AN IDIOT.

448
00:27:04,755 --> 00:27:05,755
- OH.

449
00:27:05,756 --> 00:27:07,056
squeak!

450
00:27:09,794 --> 00:27:11,994
- CAN I HELP YOU FOLKS
FIND ANYTHING?

451
00:27:11,995 --> 00:27:13,930
- AH, YEAH.
WE'RE ACTUALLY--

452
00:27:13,931 --> 00:27:16,332
DO YOU HAVE ANY PAINT
AND DROP CLOTHS, BY ANY CHANCE?

453
00:27:16,333 --> 00:27:17,467
- I SURE DO.

454
00:27:17,468 --> 00:27:18,902
I'VE GOT SOME COLOR CHARTS
UP FRONT.

455
00:27:18,903 --> 00:27:20,703
LET'S GO TAKE A LOOK.
- OKAY.

456
00:27:33,517 --> 00:27:35,384
- I'M FRED.

457
00:27:35,385 --> 00:27:37,053
- JENNIFER, EVAN.

458
00:27:37,054 --> 00:27:38,888
- YOU'RE DOING SOME REMODELING.

459
00:27:38,889 --> 00:27:40,790
- WE JUST BOUGHT THE OLD
TUCKER PLACE UP THE ROAD.

460
00:27:40,791 --> 00:27:42,892
WE'RE GONNA BE FIXING IT UP.

461
00:27:45,629 --> 00:27:47,430
- IT'S A GRAND HOUSE.

462
00:27:47,431 --> 00:27:49,098
- GRAND, MY ASS.

463
00:27:49,099 --> 00:27:51,067
- WE CALL HIM MR. PECK.

464
00:27:51,068 --> 00:27:54,871
- SURPRISED IT'S STILL STANDING
AFTER 50 YEARS.

465
00:27:54,872 --> 00:27:56,906
- IT'S ACTUALLY
IN PRETTY GOOD SHAPE.

466
00:27:56,907 --> 00:27:57,907
- YOU DON'T SAY?

467
00:27:57,908 --> 00:27:59,642
- TUCKERS DIED IN '61.

468
00:27:59,643 --> 00:28:01,644
THE PLACE HAS BEEN ABANDONED
EVER SINCE.

469
00:28:01,645 --> 00:28:03,112
- ACTUALLY, DO YOU KNOW WHY

470
00:28:03,113 --> 00:28:05,748
THEIR FAMILIES NEVER CLAIMED
THEIR THINGS?

471
00:28:05,749 --> 00:28:08,751
- WELL, THERE WASN'T
ANY FAMILY LEFT.

472
00:28:08,752 --> 00:28:11,220
THE ESTATE,
IT DIED WHEN THEY DID.

473
00:28:11,221 --> 00:28:12,622
- HOW'D THEY GO?

474
00:28:12,623 --> 00:28:14,624
- THEY DIDN'T TELL YOU
AT THE ASSESSOR'S OFFICE?

475
00:28:14,625 --> 00:28:16,659
- THINK THEY'D HAVE BOUGHT
THE PLACE IF THEY DID?

476
00:28:16,660 --> 00:28:19,662
- GIVE IT A REST!

477
00:28:19,663 --> 00:28:21,798
I'M SORRY.

478
00:28:21,799 --> 00:28:23,500
- WHAT'S THAT ABOUT?

479
00:28:23,501 --> 00:28:27,670
- LOOK, MISTER, IT'S NOT
MY PLACE TO TALK ABOUT IT.

480
00:28:27,671 --> 00:28:28,938
I AIN'T SAYING.

481
00:28:28,939 --> 00:28:30,707
- JUST DON'T GO DIGGING
IN THE BACKYARD.

482
00:28:30,708 --> 00:28:32,475
THAT'S ALL YOU NEED TO KNOW.

483
00:28:32,476 --> 00:28:34,577
- WHY?

484
00:28:35,746 --> 00:28:39,482
- OKAY, UM,
LEMON YELLOW.

485
00:28:39,483 --> 00:28:42,719
- WHAT?
- YES. LEMON YELLOW.

486
00:28:42,720 --> 00:28:44,420
THAT'S WHAT I'D LIKE TO PAINT
MY KITCHEN.

487
00:28:44,421 --> 00:28:45,588
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

488
00:28:45,589 --> 00:28:47,056
- WITH A LITTLE SEMIGLOSS
WHITE TRIM,

489
00:28:47,057 --> 00:28:48,992
YOU'LL HAVE A BEAUTIFUL KITCHEN
IS WHAT I THINK.

490
00:28:48,993 --> 00:28:50,760
AND I'LL DIG UP A COUPLE GALLONS
OF THE STUFF,

491
00:28:50,761 --> 00:28:51,928
AND I'LL BRING IT BY TOMORROW.

492
00:28:51,929 --> 00:28:52,929
- THANK YOU.

493
00:28:52,930 --> 00:28:54,564
COME ON.

494
00:28:54,565 --> 00:28:56,065
THANK YOU.

495
00:28:56,066 --> 00:28:58,568
- I REALLY HOPE YOU KIDS BRING
SOME LIGHT BACK TO THAT HOUSE.

496
00:28:58,569 --> 00:29:02,204
IT'S HAD A DARK CLOUD OVER IT
FOR A LONG TIME.

497
00:29:02,205 --> 00:29:04,206
squeak!
- WE'LL TRY.

498
00:29:04,207 --> 00:29:06,009
- PUT THAT DOWN.

499
00:29:11,615 --> 00:29:13,315
[bells chime]

500
00:29:13,316 --> 00:29:16,152
- LET ME KNOW WHEN...

501
00:29:16,153 --> 00:29:17,720
WHEN YOU FIND THOSE PAINTS.

502
00:29:17,721 --> 00:29:18,855
I'LL TAKE IT OVER.

503
00:29:18,856 --> 00:29:20,590
- WHY WOULD YOU WANT TO DO THAT
TO YOURSELF?

504
00:29:20,591 --> 00:29:22,491
- I WANT TO MAKE SURE WHAT WAS
BURIED STAYS BURIED.

505
00:29:22,492 --> 00:29:23,526
- [inhales deeply]

506
00:29:23,527 --> 00:29:25,461
