BUT YOU MEAN TO TELL ME THAT
KEN AND HILLARY CLEANED UP?

1000
00:55:04,900 --> 00:55:06,801
- I DON'T THINK THAT SOUNDS
LIKE HILLARY.

1001
00:55:06,802 --> 00:55:09,738
- NO.

1002
00:55:09,739 --> 00:55:12,140
- A LITTLE SALT AND PEPPER
FOR YOU.

1003
00:55:12,141 --> 00:55:16,844
- OH, EVAN, I DON'T USUALLY
EAT BREAKFAST THIS EARLY.

1004
00:55:19,448 --> 00:55:20,448
- JEN?

1005
00:55:20,449 --> 00:55:22,550
- OH, THANK YOU.

1006
00:55:22,551 --> 00:55:24,753
OKAY.

1007
00:55:26,822 --> 00:55:29,357
SO WHAT ARE YOU BOYS UP TO
TODAY?

1008
00:55:29,358 --> 00:55:31,359
- WELL, WHEN MIKE
FINALLY WAKES UP,

1009
00:55:31,360 --> 00:55:32,694
WE'RE GONNA WORK
ON THE WIRING.

1010
00:55:32,695 --> 00:55:33,861
- ALL RIGHT.

1011
00:55:33,862 --> 00:55:35,497
WELL, UM, I'M GOING TO GO
INTO TOWN

1012
00:55:35,498 --> 00:55:36,498
AND RUN A FEW ERRANDS.

1013
00:55:36,499 --> 00:55:38,933
- OH, CAN I COME?
- YEAH.

1014
00:55:38,934 --> 00:55:40,034
YOU WANT ANYTHING?

1015
00:55:40,035 --> 00:55:41,803
- YEAH, CAN I GET
A DOUBLE TALL LATTE

1016
00:55:41,804 --> 00:55:43,471
AND A LOW-FAT APRICOT MUFFIN?

1017
00:55:43,472 --> 00:55:44,939
- RIGHT.

1018
00:55:44,940 --> 00:55:47,942
HOW ABOUT A BIG OLD PLATE
OF SOME CHITLINS AND CRAWFISH?

1019
00:55:47,943 --> 00:55:50,144
- MMM.
CRAWFISH.

1020
00:55:50,145 --> 00:55:51,479
- [laughs]

1021
00:55:51,480 --> 00:55:53,682
THANK YOU SO MUCH FOR BREAKFAST.
THAT WAS REALLY SWEET.

1022
00:55:53,683 --> 00:55:56,618
- MM-HMM.

1023
00:55:56,619 --> 00:56:00,121
- BYE.
- HA!

1024
00:56:00,122 --> 00:56:01,122
- BYE.

1025
00:56:01,123 --> 00:56:04,125
[pleasant mandolin music]

1026
00:56:04,126 --> 00:56:12,066
 

1027
00:56:15,971 --> 00:56:18,706
- GOD BLESS AMERICA.

1028
00:56:18,707 --> 00:56:20,041
LET'S EAT.

1029
00:56:20,042 --> 00:56:22,377
- YEAH, HEY, PICK UP
WHATEVER YOU THINK WE NEED.

1030
00:56:22,378 --> 00:56:24,112
I'M JUST GONNA GO
CHECK OUT SOMETHING.

1031
00:56:24,113 --> 00:56:26,114
- COOL.

1032
00:56:26,115 --> 00:56:34,055
 

1033
00:56:42,097 --> 00:56:45,099
[eerie music]

1034
00:56:45,100 --> 00:56:50,205
 

1035
00:56:50,206 --> 00:56:52,307
MR. PECK?

1036
00:57:09,392 --> 00:57:11,459
MR. PECK?

1037
00:57:21,537 --> 00:57:23,538
MR. PECK?

1038
00:57:38,387 --> 00:57:42,257
- FIND WHAT YOU'RE LOOKING FOR?

1039
00:57:42,258 --> 00:57:44,326
- I'M SORRY.

1040
00:57:44,327 --> 00:57:47,662
I GUESS I'M NOT USED TO SEEING
WHERE MY FOOD COMES FROM.

1041
00:57:51,334 --> 00:57:53,735
- THAT'S WHY WE, UH--

1042
00:57:53,736 --> 00:57:56,238
THAT'S WHY WE DO IT OUT HERE.

1043
00:57:56,239 --> 00:57:58,607
WANT A DRINK?

1044
00:57:58,608 --> 00:58:02,043
- I'M GOOD.

1045
00:58:02,044 --> 00:58:03,878
- I KNOW WHY YOU'RE HERE.

1046
00:58:03,879 --> 00:58:06,281
- I WANT TO KNOW
WHY YOU RAN YESTERDAY.

1047
00:58:06,282 --> 00:58:08,116
- I HAD TO GET TO WORK.

1048
00:58:08,117 --> 00:58:09,851
- MR. PECK, I KNOW
THAT THERE'S SOMETHING

1049
00:58:09,852 --> 00:58:12,820
THAT YOU'RE NOT TELLING ME.

1050
00:58:12,821 --> 00:58:14,556
I FOUND A DIARY.

1051
00:58:14,557 --> 00:58:16,691
IT'S A WOMAN'S:

1052
00:58:16,692 --> 00:58:17,659
LYDIA BEAUMONT.

1053
00:58:23,466 --> 00:58:26,000
YOU KNEW HER.

1054
00:58:29,272 --> 00:58:31,573
- I KILLED HER.

1055
00:58:34,443 --> 00:58:36,378
- WHY?

1056
00:58:36,379 --> 00:58:38,313
- GIVE ME MY BABY!

1057
00:58:38,314 --> 00:58:40,382
[gunshot]

1058
00:58:40,383 --> 00:58:42,384
- SHE WAS A WITCH.

1059
00:58:42,385 --> 00:58:43,485
- THERE'S NO SUCH THING.

1060
00:58:43,486 --> 00:58:44,786
- I WOULD HAVE SAID
THE SAME THING

1061
00:58:44,787 --> 00:58:47,121
IF I HAVEN'T SEEN IT
WITH MY OWN EYES.

1062
00:58:47,122 --> 00:58:48,923
HELL, I EVEN DEFENDED HER.

1063
00:58:48,924 --> 00:58:53,662
WHEN THE ANIMALS,
WHEN THEY CAME UP MISSING,

1064
00:58:53,663 --> 00:58:56,631
PEOPLE SAID IT WAS
FOR HER VOODOO.

1065
00:58:56,632 --> 00:58:57,965
I SAID IT WAS A FOX.

1066
00:58:57,966 --> 00:58:59,934
WELL, I WAS WRONG.

1067
00:58:59,935 --> 00:59:01,936
- SHE WAS KILLING
FARM ANIMALS?

1068
00:59:01,937 --> 00:59:05,907
- SACRIFICING THEM,
MORE LIKE IT.

1069
00:59:05,908 --> 00:59:07,375
I MEAN, MAYBE
IT WOULD HAVE BEEN OKAY

1070
00:59:07,376 --> 00:59:10,578
IF IT STAYED
WITH CHICKENS AND GOATS,

1071
00:59:10,579 --> 00:59:13,748
BUT THEN THAT'S WHEN
THE TOWNFOLK

1072
00:59:13,749 --> 00:59:15,850
TOOK THE LAW
INTO THEIR OWN HANDS.

1073
00:59:15,851 --> 00:59:17,852
THE BOY GOT SICK,

1074
00:59:17,853 --> 00:59:20,322
UGLY SICK.

1075
00:59:20,323 --> 00:59:24,158
PEOPLE SAID THAT
IT MADE HER MAD,

1076
00:59:24,159 --> 00:59:25,960
CRAZY.

1077
00:59:25,961 --> 00:59:29,698
- LEONARD, RIGHT?
- YEAH. LEONARD.

1078
00:59:32,468 --> 00:59:37,572
- WHAT WAS WRONG WITH HIM?

1079
00:59:37,573 --> 00:59:39,607
- HE WAS DEVIL-TOUCHED.

1080
00:59:39,608 --> 00:59:41,343
IT'S THE ONLY WORD
TO DESCRIBE HIM--

1081
00:59:41,344 --> 00:59:43,244
HIM AND HIS MOTHER.

1082
00:59:47,650 --> 00:59:48,750
- [crying]

1083
00:59:48,751 --> 00:59:51,285
- SHE STOLE MY BABY.

1084
00:59:51,286 --> 00:59:53,154
SACRIFICED HIM
IN THE NAME OF MAGIC,

1085
00:59:53,155 --> 00:59:59,126
ALL TO SAVE THAT EVIL
BASTARD OF HERS.

1086
00:59:59,127 --> 01:00:01,363
THE ONLY THING IN THE WORLD
THAT I WANTED

1087
01:00:01,364 --> 01:00:04,265
WAS TO SAVE MY BABY,

1088
01:00:04,266 --> 01:00:09,036
AND THAT ONE WAS TOO LATE
FOR THAT.

1089
01:00:09,037 --> 01:00:13,541
ALL I WANTED TO SEE
WAS HER BURNED.

1090
01:00:13,542 --> 01:00:17,412
- [screaming]

1091
01:00:26,655 --> 01:00:30,492
- YOU GOTTA LEAVE THAT HOUSE.

1092
01:00:30,493 --> 01:00:34,863
DO YOU HEAR ME?

1093
01:00:34,864 --> 01:00:37,699
YOU GOTTA LEAVE THAT HOUSE.

1094
01:00:37,700 --> 01:00:40,368
HE'S COMING BACK
TO AVENGE HIS MOTHER.

1095
01:00:40,369 --> 01:00:42,336
YOU HEAR ME?

1096
01:00:42,337 --> 01:00:43,605
HUH?

1097
01:00:43,606 --> 01:00:45,807
[shouting]
YOU HEAR ME?

1098
01:00:45,808 --> 01:00:48,576
HE'LL KILL YOU ALL!
YOU HEAR ME?

1099
01:00:48,577 --> 01:00:49,577
- AH!

1100
01:00:49,578 --> 01:00:51,178
- JESUS.

1101
01:00:51,179 --> 01:00:52,614
YOU OKAY?

1102
01:00:52,615 --> 01:00:55,683
- YES, JUST SOME SERIOUSLY
FUCKED-UP PEOPLE IN THIS TOWN.

1103
01:00:55,684 --> 01:00:59,587
- WHAT HAPPENED?

1104
01:00:59,588 --> 01:01:00,822
JEN, WHAT HAPPENED?

1105
01:01:00,823 --> 01:01:02,824
- I DON'T KNOW.
JUST, LET'S GO.

1106
01:01:02,825 --> 01:01:05,660
I'M REALLY STARTING
TO HATE THIS PLACE.

1107
01:01:13,536 --> 01:01:15,236
- I THINK JEN'S STARTING
TO LIKE THIS PLACE.

1108
01:01:15,237 --> 01:01:16,471
- YEAH?
THAT'S GOOD, MAN.

1109
01:01:16,472 --> 01:01:17,806
- HEY, WOULD YOU HAND ME
A BULB?

1110
01:01:17,807 --> 01:01:19,507
- UH...

1111
01:01:19,508 --> 01:01:21,576
KIND OF BUSY;
GIVE ME A SECOND.

1112
01:01:21,577 --> 01:01:23,244
- DUDE, JUST HAND ME A BULB,
YOU HOMO.

1113
01:01:23,245 --> 01:01:24,245
- [drops tool]

1114
01:01:24,246 --> 01:01:25,413
DAMN IT.
DAMN IT.

1115
01:01:25,414 --> 01:01:27,014
YOU SUCK.

1116
01:01:27,015 --> 01:01:29,150
YOU KNOW, YOU GUYS
SHOULD REALLY THINK

1117
01:01:29,151 --> 01:01:31,052
ABOUT REDOING ALL THE WIRING
IN HERE...

1118
01:01:31,053 --> 01:01:34,622
I MEAN, IF YOU'RE EVER PLANNING
ON SELLING IT.

1119
01:01:34,623 --> 01:01:36,090
- HEY, GIVE ME THE BULB.

1120
01:01:36,091 --> 01:01:38,560
- OH, SHIT.
HERE.

1121
01:01:38,561 --> 01:01:40,962
I STILL CAN'T BELIEVE THAT
YOU PUT THE DEED IN HER NAME.

1122
01:01:40,963 --> 01:01:42,997
THAT'S JUST LIKE NOT GETTING HER
TO SIGN A PRE-NUP.

1123
01:01:42,998 --> 01:01:43,998
- AHA!

1124
01:01:43,999 --> 01:01:44,999
smack

1125
01:01:45,000 --> 01:01:46,334
- OH.

1126
01:01:46,335 --> 01:01:49,170
DUDE.

1127
01:01:49,171 --> 01:01:50,204
- THANKS, BRO.

1128
01:01:50,205 --> 01:01:51,205
- I'LL GO CHECK THE BOX.

1129
01:01:51,206 --> 01:01:52,440
- YEAH, PLEASE DO.

1130
01:01:52,441 --> 01:01:54,509
- [growling]

1131
01:01:54,510 --> 01:01:57,378
[metal scraping]

1132
01:02:01,450 --> 01:02:02,450
- WHERE IS IT?

1133
01:02:02,451 --> 01:02:03,451
DID IT WORK?

1134
01:02:03,452 --> 01:02:04,452
- DID YOU FLIP IT?

1135
01:02:04,453 --> 01:02:05,487
- YEAH. FLIPPED IT.

1136
01:02:05,488 --> 01:02:07,021
- LOOKS LIKE THE WIRES
ARE CROSSED.

1137
01:02:07,022 --> 01:02:08,490
PROBABLY SOMEWHERE
IN THE BASEMENT.

1138
01:02:08,491 --> 01:02:10,157
SEE HOW IT RUNS DOWN?

1139
01:02:10,158 --> 01:02:12,660
I'LL GO CHECK IT OUT.

1140
01:02:12,661 --> 01:02:14,161
- IF YOU'RE NOT BACK IN A WEEK,

1141
01:02:14,162 --> 01:02:15,162
I'LL DRAG THE LAKE.

1142
01:02:15,163 --> 01:02:16,998
- YEAH, ALL RIGHT.

1143
01:02:16,999 --> 01:02:20,167
- AND STAY OUT OF THAT WINE!

1144
01:02:20,168 --> 01:02:23,170
[eerie music]

1145
01:02:23,171 --> 01:02:31,112
 

1146
01:02:49,765 --> 01:02:51,799
- HELLO?

1147
01:03:14,557 --> 01:03:17,058
HOLY SHIT.

1148
01:03:21,129 --> 01:03:23,398
FUCK ME.

1149
01:03:23,399 --> 01:03:24,865
OH.

1150
01:03:24,866 --> 01:03:27,267
EVAN'S GONNA FLIP HIS SHIT.

1151
01:03:27,268 --> 01:03:29,169
YO, "E"!

1152
01:03:31,272 --> 01:03:33,340
OH, MY GOD.

1153
01:03:43,418 --> 01:03:46,253
- [grumbles]

1154
01:03:46,254 --> 01:03:47,254
- [laughs nervously]

1155
01:03:47,255 --> 01:03:48,355
OH, SHIT.

1156
01:03:48,356 --> 01:03:51,492
OH, DUDE, THAT WAS--
YOU SCARED ME.

1157
01:03:51,493 --> 01:03:53,060
ALL RIGHT, YOU GOT ME.

1158
01:03:53,061 --> 01:03:56,597
WE'RE EVEN.

1159
01:03:56,598 --> 01:03:59,466
UGH!

1160
01:03:59,467 --> 01:04:00,501
- HEY, MIKE!

1161
01:04:00,502 --> 01:04:02,269
I TOLD YOU STAY AWAY
FROM MY WINE.

1162
01:04:02,270 --> 01:04:04,005
- [moaning]

1163
01:04:04,006 --> 01:04:07,407
- FRIGGIN' DRUNK.

1164
01:04:07,408 --> 01:04:09,610
- YOU FUCKER!

1165
01:04:09,611 --> 01:04:11,846
FUCK!

1166
01:04:11,847 --> 01:04:13,047
NO!

1167
01:04:13,048 --> 01:04:16,984
[moaning]

1168
01:04:31,299 --> 01:04:34,334
- MIKE.

1169
01:04:34,335 --> 01:04:36,904
GOD DAMN IT.

1170
01:04:40,976 --> 01:04:44,378
MIKE!

1171
01:04:44,379 --> 01:04:47,148
MIKE!

1172
01:04:47,149 --> 01:04:49,216
SWEAR TO GOD, IF YOU THROW
THAT SCARECROW AT ME AGAIN,

1173
01:04:49,217 --> 01:04:54,955
I'M GONNA PUNCH YOU
IN THE SAC.

1174
01:04:54,956 --> 01:04:56,190
COME ON, MIKE.

1175
01:04:56,191 --> 01:04:58,926
IT'S NOT FUNNY ANYMORE.
WE GOT STUFF TO DO.

1176
01:05:05,901 --> 01:05:08,002
YOU GOT THE DOOR OPEN, HUH?

1177
01:05:08,003 --> 01:05:09,436
WHERE'D YOU FIND THE KEY?

1178
01:05:09,437 --> 01:05:12,539
MIKE?
WHERE ARE YOU?

1179
01:05:14,576 --> 01:05:18,478
HEY, I SEE YOU, DIPSHIT.

1180
01:05:18,479 --> 01:05:22,149
ALL RIGHT, ENJOY THE SMELL.
I'M LOCKING YOU IN.

1181
01:05:32,660 --> 01:05:34,328
WHAT'S UP WITH YOUR FACE?

1182
01:05:34,329 --> 01:05:37,264
- [grumbling]

1183
01:05:45,807 --> 01:05:48,408
- [screams]

1184
01:05:51,346 --> 01:05:53,881
HEY! HELP!

1185
01:05:53,882 --> 01:05:55,249
AH!

1186
01:05:55,250 --> 01:05:56,951
SOMEBODY HELP ME!

1187
01:06:03,925 --> 01:06:06,927
[tense percussive music]

1188
01:06:06,928 --> 01:06:14,869
 

1189
01:06:24,179 --> 01:06:28,448
[breathing heavily]

1190
01:06:28,449 --> 01:06:29,716
- [growling]

1191
01:06:35,924 --> 01:06:36,957
crack!

1192
01:06:38,794 --> 01:06:39,794
crack!

1193
01:06:39,795 --> 01:06:42,897
UGH!

1194
01:06:42,898 --> 01:06:46,834
- AH!

1195
01:06:46,835 --> 01:06:48,568
UGH!

1196
01:06:48,569 --> 01:06:51,571
[dramatic music]

1197
01:06:51,572 --> 01:06:59,513
 

1198
01:07:37,785 --> 01:07:42,756
 

1199
01:07:42,757 --> 01:07:45,993
- OH!

1200
01:07:45,994 --> 01:07:47,794
OH!

1201
01:08:00,441 --> 01:08:03,610
- WHO'S THE CREEPER?

1202
01:08:03,611 --> 01:08:05,880
- IT'S OKAY.
I KNOW HIM.

1203
01:08:05,881 --> 01:08:06,881
- YEAH?
- YEAH.

1204
01:08:06,882 --> 01:08:08,182
COULD YOU PULL THE CAR AROUND?

1205
01:08:08,183 --> 01:08:09,283
- YEAH.

1206
01:08:09,284 --> 01:08:10,751
HEY, SCREAM IF YOU NEED ME,
ALL RIGHT?

1207
01:08:10,752 --> 01:08:14,855
- YEAH, I'LL MEET YOU INSIDE.

1208
01:08:14,856 --> 01:08:16,357
- I DON'T MEAN TO BOTHER YOU,

1209
01:08:16,358 --> 01:08:20,127
BUT YOU HAVEN'T SEEN MR. PECK
OUT HERE TODAY, HAVE YOU?

1210
01:08:20,128 --> 01:08:22,729
- ACTUALLY, I JUST LEFT HIM
DOWN AT THE STORE.

1211
01:08:22,730 --> 01:08:27,268
HE--HE WAS REALLY DRUNK
AND ACTING PRETTY STRANGE.

1212
01:08:27,269 --> 01:08:28,535
- IT'S THIS PLACE.

1213
01:08:28,536 --> 01:08:31,105
IT DREDGES UP A LOT
OF REALLY BAD MEMORIES FOR HIM.

1214
01:08:31,106 --> 01:08:34,375
- YEAH, HE TOLD ME...
EVERYTHING.

1215
01:08:36,411 --> 01:08:38,178
- EVAN?

1216
01:08:42,250 --> 01:08:44,084
MIKE?

1217
01:08:54,162 --> 01:08:57,731
HELLO?

1218
01:08:57,732 --> 01:09:00,734
[ominous music]

1219
01:09:00,735 --> 01:09:08,475
 

1220
01:09:09,544 --> 01:09:13,147
[laughing]

1221
01:09:13,148 --> 01:09:16,483
"FOR YOU."

1222
01:09:16,484 --> 01:09:19,053
IT LOOKS LIKE A KINDERGARTENER
WROTE IT.

1223
01:09:19,054 --> 01:09:23,890
[water running]

1224
01:09:23,891 --> 01:09:26,493
MIKE?

1225
01:09:26,494 --> 01:09:29,063
MIKE?

1226
01:09:29,064 --> 01:09:32,866
COME OUT, COME OUT,
WHEREVER YOU ARE.

1227
01:09:39,740 --> 01:09:41,808
- IF YOU DO SEE HIM,

1228
01:09:41,809 --> 01:09:43,210
YOU'LL GIVE ME A CALL, RIGHT?

1229
01:09:43,211 --> 01:09:45,212
- OKAY.
I'LL DO THAT.

1230
01:09:45,213 --> 01:09:48,182
- GOOD.

1231
01:09:48,183 --> 01:09:49,883
- HEY, FRED.

1232
01:09:49,884 --> 01:09:51,952
WHAT IS MR. PECK SO AFRAID OF?

1233
01:09:56,224 --> 01:09:59,659
- THE PAST.

1234
01:10:09,271 --> 01:10:12,273
[eerie music]

1235
01:10:12,274 --> 01:10:20,214
 

1236
01:10:26,288 --> 01:10:27,655
crash!

1237
01:10:35,730 --> 01:10:39,066
[water running]

1238
01:10:55,217 --> 01:10:58,419
- [sighing]

1239
01:11:10,164 --> 01:11:13,667
[door opens]

1240
01:11:13,668 --> 01:11:16,670
[ominous music]

1241
01:11:16,671 --> 01:11:24,612
 

1242
01:11:49,036 --> 01:11:50,371
[screams]

1243
01:11:56,144 --> 01:11:58,545
- ANNETTE.

1244
01:11:58,546 --> 01:12:01,848
YOU UP HERE?

1245
01:12:11,326 --> 01:12:14,828
ANNETTE!

1246
01:12:14,829 --> 01:12:16,397
AH!

1247
01:12:21,369 --> 01:12:24,538
[crying]

1248
01:12:24,539 --> 01:12:27,541
[foreboding music]

1249
01:12:27,542 --> 01:12:35,482
 

1250
01:13:03,044 --> 01:13:06,380
- [coughing]

1251
01:13:09,451 --> 01:13:17,391
 

1252
01:13:18,827 --> 01:13:22,763
- [crying]

1253
01:13:47,154 --> 01:13:50,156
[ominous music]

1254
01:13:50,157 --> 01:13:54,828
 

1255
